checkCellForPo...omainBuffering(25.10)  checkCellForPo...omainBuffering(25.10)

Name
       checkCellForPowerDomainBuffering - Checks if the specified AO cell type
       can be used in a specific location domain

Syntax
       checkCellForPowerDomainBuffering

       [-help]

       -cell  <always_on_cell_name>{[-driver_term <term_name>] [-effective_do-
       main <effective_domain_name>]}

       -location_domain <location_domain_name>

       Checks if the specified AO cell type can be used in a specific location
       domain. Additionally, this command checks if the specified  AO  voltage
       (cell OPCOND) matches with its driving voltage (domain OPCOND).

Parameters
       -help  Prints  a  brief  description that includes the type and default
              information for each checkCellForPowerDomainBuffering parameter.
              For a detailed description of the command and  all  its  parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man checkCellForPowerDomainBuffering

       -cell <always_on_cell_name>
              Specifies the always_on_cell name.

       -driver_term <term_name>
              Specifies the AO's driver pin (leaf instance pin) name.

       -effective_domain <effective_domain_name>
              Specifies the AO sink's effective domain name.

       -location_domain <location_domain_name>
              Specifies  the  name of the location domain where AO is going to
              be inserted.

